.TH "bcom_psc_gen_bd_rx_init" 9 "bcom_psc_gen_bd_rx_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcom_psc_gen_bd_rx_init \- Allocate a receive bcom_task for a PSC port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct bcom_task *" bcom_psc_gen_bd_rx_init
.BI "(unsigned psc_num "  ","
.BI "int queue_len "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t fifo "  ","
.BI "int maxbufsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "psc_num" 12
Number of the PSC to allocate a task for
.IP "queue_len" 12
number of buffer descriptors to allocate for the task
.IP "fifo" 12
physical address of FIFO register
.IP "maxbufsize" 12
Maximum receive data size in bytes.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a bestcomm task structure for receiving data from a PSC.
